1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,669
[Locsin] <i>Looks like</i>
<i>your hand got hurt pretty bad?</i>

2
00:00:02,752 --> 00:00:05,213
<i>I do not even know</i>
<i>how I managed to face him.</i>

3
00:00:05,296 --> 00:00:07,632
<i>All I could think about</i>
<i>was getting Seth back.</i>

4
00:00:09,342 --> 00:00:10,844
<i>You should not have faced him alone.</i>

5
00:00:10,927 --> 00:00:12,470
<i>You should have called Uncle Edward.</i>

6
00:00:12,554 --> 00:00:14,139
<i>Or at least asked for help.</i>

7
00:00:14,222 --> 00:00:15,432
<i>He was holding Seth, Erica.</i>

8
00:00:15,515 --> 00:00:16,850
<i>I didn't even think--</i>

9
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:17,934
<i>He's a murderer.</i>

10
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:19,894
<i>Be grateful that's all</i>
<i>that happened to you.</i>

11
00:00:19,978 --> 00:00:22,605
<i>Althea? What happened?</i>

12
00:00:22,689 --> 00:00:23,982
<i>You have to leave.</i>

13
00:00:24,065 --> 00:00:26,276
<i>You and Seth need to go back to the US.</i>

14
00:00:26,359 --> 00:00:29,404
<i>We cannot give</i>
<i>that monster another chance at our son.</i>

15
00:00:29,487 --> 00:00:30,822
[Beth] <i>We need to work together.</i>

16
00:00:30,905 --> 00:00:32,907
<i>All our lives are in danger,</i>

17
00:00:32,991 --> 00:00:34,868
<i>including the people we love.</i>

18
00:00:34,951 --> 00:00:36,828
<i>We need to stop Edong now.</i>

19
00:00:36,911 --> 00:00:41,416
[suspenseful music playing]

20
00:00:42,709 --> 00:00:49,215
[theme music playing]

21
00:01:57,909 --> 00:02:02,455
[sinister music playing]

22
00:02:23,768 --> 00:02:25,145
- [man] Edward!
- [music fades]

23
00:02:27,689 --> 00:02:29,149
- [rooster crows]
- How are you guys?

24
00:02:30,108 --> 00:02:31,818
I heard what happened. That was terrible.

25
00:02:32,277 --> 00:02:33,736
How's your grandson?

26
00:02:33,820 --> 00:02:35,738
Luckily, he didn't get hurt much.

27
00:02:35,822 --> 00:02:37,365
[exhales] He's okay now

28
00:02:37,448 --> 00:02:40,160
but, of course, the child was traumatized.

29
00:02:40,827 --> 00:02:42,162
I'm glad you got him back.

30
00:02:42,745 --> 00:02:44,164
But what you did was admirable.

31
00:02:44,247 --> 00:02:46,374
You were able to fight that person.

32
00:02:49,168 --> 00:02:50,962
When it comes to family,

33
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:53,339
we do anything we possibly can.

34
00:02:53,923 --> 00:02:54,841
[rooster crows]

35
00:02:54,924 --> 00:02:58,136
Good thing
our village added more security.

36
00:02:58,219 --> 00:02:59,596
[rooster crows]

37
00:02:59,679 --> 00:03:01,097
Who knows,

38
00:03:01,180 --> 00:03:03,641
Edong might attack our neighbors again.

39
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:05,852
It's worrisome.

40
00:03:08,438 --> 00:03:09,689
[Erica] You heard that?

41
00:03:10,481 --> 00:03:12,901
I was behind Cornelio when he was talking.

42
00:03:12,984 --> 00:03:14,527
[tense music playing]

43
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:16,487
It was probably Travis.

44
00:03:16,571 --> 00:03:18,406
He is Kyle's number one apologist.

45
00:03:19,908 --> 00:03:21,075
When we went to see him,

46
00:03:21,159 --> 00:03:22,493
he was defensive for Kyle.

47
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:26,539
Cornelio warned him
that you guys were coming.

48
00:03:27,415 --> 00:03:29,042
They were talking about something

49
00:03:29,125 --> 00:03:30,627
that needs to be kept secret from you.

50
00:03:30,710 --> 00:03:33,838
[tense music continues]

51
00:03:33,922 --> 00:03:35,924
[Marco] We need to monitor them.

52
00:03:36,007 --> 00:03:37,508
Even Kyle's mother.

53
00:03:38,218 --> 00:03:41,054
Do you think that will reveal anything?

54
00:03:42,513 --> 00:03:44,015
Kyle is currently in the US.

55
00:03:44,933 --> 00:03:48,853
They are our only physical link
to what happened 14 years ago.

56
00:03:49,854 --> 00:03:51,940
[Marco] What's clear is
we got a reaction from them.

57
00:03:53,441 --> 00:03:55,318
We just have to wait
and see what they do next.

58
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:00,490
[car door opens, closes]

59
00:04:00,573 --> 00:04:05,745
[tense music continues]

60
00:04:15,713 --> 00:04:20,385
[tense music continues]

61
00:04:20,468 --> 00:04:22,679
- [Marco] I have spoken to the police.
- [music fades]

62
00:04:22,762 --> 00:04:24,597
They don't want
to panic the people of Amurao,

63
00:04:24,681 --> 00:04:25,640
like what happened before.

64
00:04:25,723 --> 00:04:28,518
They're worried
it might bring bigger trouble.

65
00:04:28,601 --> 00:04:31,187
But they will search every
area where Edong could be hiding.

66
00:04:32,188 --> 00:04:34,649
Even Louisa and
Liezel's spot by the woods.

67
00:04:35,692 --> 00:04:38,152
Since Edong knows about it,
the cops will search it too.

68
00:04:38,778 --> 00:04:41,572
Erica and I went to our old home.
There's no one there.

69
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:46,327
[uneasy music playing]

70
00:04:47,078 --> 00:04:48,871
We still need to get it checked.

71
00:04:49,998 --> 00:04:51,249
Like I said,

72
00:04:51,332 --> 00:04:53,501
they will do everything to find him.

73
00:04:54,877 --> 00:04:57,297
You said… that's what you wanted, right?

74
00:04:57,380 --> 00:04:59,299
[tense music resumes]

75
00:04:59,382 --> 00:05:00,842
[car engine revving]

76
00:05:00,925 --> 00:05:02,343
[tires screech]

77
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:03,469
Hands up!

78
00:05:06,639 --> 00:05:07,974
Sir! Please don't!

79
00:05:08,057 --> 00:05:11,978
[tense music continues]

80
00:05:16,357 --> 00:05:17,442
Take a look at this.

81
00:05:18,693 --> 00:05:19,819
Go around the area.

82
00:05:20,611 --> 00:05:22,196
[Lucas] Like I told Erica,

83
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:24,741
my brother won't ever go to our old house.

84
00:05:25,575 --> 00:05:28,286
Because that's where
my father killed my mother.

85
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:34,876
But if you want to waste your time…

86
00:05:36,085 --> 00:05:37,003
Then go.

87
00:05:37,086 --> 00:05:41,924
[uneasy music playing]

88
00:05:43,092 --> 00:05:44,886
Amurao isn't that big, right?

89
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:48,723
Maybe the police aren't that stupid
and catch him right away.

90
00:05:51,601 --> 00:05:53,728
- [phone buzzing]
- [music fades]

91
00:05:54,896 --> 00:05:55,855
Hello?

92
00:05:58,441 --> 00:05:59,734
[sighs in relief] Thank you.

93
00:06:02,904 --> 00:06:04,572
The prosecutor found
something for us to continue

94
00:06:04,655 --> 00:06:06,574
our case against Anton.

95
00:06:06,657 --> 00:06:11,079
[stirring music playing]

96
00:06:13,164 --> 00:06:15,249
[Mel inhales, exhales heavily]

97
00:06:21,380 --> 00:06:23,800
You said you had
influence at the Justice Department!

98
00:06:23,883 --> 00:06:26,594
They did speed up the resolution,
but they'll still sue me?!

99
00:06:26,677 --> 00:06:27,845
I don't know what happened.

100
00:06:27,929 --> 00:06:31,099
I've been calling Secretary,
but he's not answering!

101
00:06:31,474 --> 00:06:32,975
This shouldn't be happening.

102
00:06:33,684 --> 00:06:36,771
Okay, but don't worry.
Attorney Artillero will--

103
00:06:36,854 --> 00:06:37,980
It shouldn't have come to this

104
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:39,774
if you just did what you promised!

105
00:06:39,857 --> 00:06:42,568
Hey! I told you from the beginning.

106
00:06:42,652 --> 00:06:44,779
That woman was no good for you!

107
00:06:44,862 --> 00:06:48,533
But did you listen? No!
Now look at what's happening!

108
00:06:48,616 --> 00:06:50,409
So you shouldn't be mad at me

109
00:06:50,493 --> 00:06:53,371
'cause this is all your fault!

110
00:06:54,831 --> 00:06:55,873
[Barbara huffs]

111
00:06:57,625 --> 00:07:02,004
[tense music playing]

112
00:07:03,464 --> 00:07:06,717
Son, I'm sorry. You didn't deserve that.

113
00:07:06,801 --> 00:07:09,846
I'm sorry. I'll fix this. Okay?

114
00:07:10,513 --> 00:07:11,722
I'll fix this.

115
00:07:11,806 --> 00:07:13,182
I'm sorry.

116
00:07:13,266 --> 00:07:14,642
I'm sorry, okay?

117
00:07:15,393 --> 00:07:18,646
I'll fix this, don't worry. I'll fix this.

118
00:07:19,981 --> 00:07:22,900
[tense music sting]

119
00:07:22,984 --> 00:07:24,068
[Alice] We were all there.

120
00:07:24,569 --> 00:07:26,487
<i>We saw how he tricked Mel,</i>

121
00:07:26,571 --> 00:07:28,614
<i>and purposefully separated her from us</i>

122
00:07:28,698 --> 00:07:30,783
<i>just so he could hurt her.</i>

123
00:07:31,534 --> 00:07:33,703
<i>Luckily, we arrived right away.</i>

124
00:07:33,786 --> 00:07:36,831
<i>Because if not, he might've killed Mel.</i>

125
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:39,083
<i>And Mel was telling the truth.</i>

126
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:41,461
<i>Don't just fall</i>

127
00:07:41,544 --> 00:07:44,672
<i>for the charming smile, the handsome face,</i>

128
00:07:44,755 --> 00:07:48,050
<i>and the edited and</i>
<i>spliced videos of that man.</i>

129
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:52,388
<i>This is not an online fan war.</i>
<i>This is about a woman's life.</i>

130
00:07:53,264 --> 00:07:54,932
<i>We will stand by Mel's side…</i>

131
00:07:55,766 --> 00:07:58,019
<i>…as she fights</i>
<i>to finally hold Anton accountable</i>

132
00:07:58,102 --> 00:08:00,396
<i>for all the abuse</i>
<i>that he has inflicted on her</i>

133
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,647
<i>all of these years.</i>

134
00:08:01,731 --> 00:08:05,943
[poignant music playing]

135
00:08:10,114 --> 00:08:11,699
[music fades]

136
00:08:11,782 --> 00:08:13,534
Are you sure about this?

137
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:16,787
If you post this online,

138
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:18,789
you'll be going
through the same toxic bullshit

139
00:08:18,873 --> 00:08:20,541
that I've been going through.

140
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:22,335
I'm used to toxic, Mel.

141
00:08:22,418 --> 00:08:25,004
Don't worry. I know how to handle this.

142
00:08:26,672 --> 00:08:30,343
Besides, is there anything more toxic
than our current situation?

143
00:08:30,885 --> 00:08:32,553
What's the difference
adding another one, right?

144
00:08:32,637 --> 00:08:34,263
[Erica chuckles wryly]

145
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:36,224
It's not even a choice, Mel.

146
00:08:38,476 --> 00:08:39,435
[Alice sighs]

147
00:08:41,479 --> 00:08:43,648
We may disagree on a lot of things…

148
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:45,441
But this?

149
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:48,194
We're a hundred percent on this.

150
00:08:50,196 --> 00:08:53,074
Right, Beth? Erica?

151
00:08:55,743 --> 00:08:57,286
There are men really like that.

152
00:08:58,704 --> 00:09:00,748
Kyle did this to Louisa back then.

153
00:09:01,332 --> 00:09:03,125
[Erica] Anton did it to you.

154
00:09:03,709 --> 00:09:05,336
If we don't fight back,

155
00:09:05,711 --> 00:09:07,922
we'll just keep letting them do this.

156
00:09:08,005 --> 00:09:09,382
This won't end.

157
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:14,387
[somber music playing]

158
00:09:14,470 --> 00:09:16,514
[Mel sniffles, sighs]

159
00:09:16,597 --> 00:09:20,059
I- I don't think I've thanked you yet.

160
00:09:22,186 --> 00:09:24,397
Like, really thank you…

161
00:09:25,523 --> 00:09:28,985
…for jumping in and
physically protecting me from my husband.

162
00:09:29,068 --> 00:09:30,570
[Mel] You got hurt, too, but…

163
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:32,863
But you didn't think about that.

164
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:37,159
Thank you.

165
00:09:37,743 --> 00:09:38,703
Thank you, guys.

166
00:09:41,163 --> 00:09:42,290
And you're right.

167
00:09:42,999 --> 00:09:44,250
We're not the same.

168
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:49,213
And we will never be after Louisa's death.

169
00:09:51,465 --> 00:09:53,050
She will always connect us.

170
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:57,471
[Mel sniffles, cries]

171
00:09:57,555 --> 00:09:58,681
That night…

172
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:02,268
That night will always connect us.

173
00:10:02,351 --> 00:10:06,981
[somber music continues]

174
00:10:17,116 --> 00:10:18,409
[Alice] How are you and Ryan?

175
00:10:18,492 --> 00:10:19,744
[music fades]

176
00:10:21,287 --> 00:10:22,455
We're going to be okay.

177
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:25,416
[sighs] Beth, I'm sorry. I…

178
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:29,003
I didn't mean to cause any
conflict between you and him.

179
00:10:31,213 --> 00:10:34,258
We can handle it. We'll be okay.

180
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:41,140
Like I said, you're right.

181
00:10:42,725 --> 00:10:44,644
I was just thinking of myself.

182
00:10:45,686 --> 00:10:48,439
I realized it after
what happened to Chloe.

183
00:10:51,442 --> 00:10:53,444
I'll help you find Edong.

184
00:10:54,987 --> 00:10:56,947
And if it's necessary to look back

185
00:10:57,031 --> 00:10:59,742
at what happened to Louisa in the past,
so we can catch him,

186
00:11:00,868 --> 00:11:01,786
then okay.

187
00:11:03,537 --> 00:11:04,580
What about…

188
00:11:05,915 --> 00:11:07,416
admitting to what we did?

189
00:11:09,710 --> 00:11:11,879
I thought we were done with that option?

190
00:11:13,339 --> 00:11:15,341
Because of Mel's situation, yes.

191
00:11:16,050 --> 00:11:18,427
However, since there
is a case against Anton,

192
00:11:18,511 --> 00:11:21,472
we might be able to convince her to do so.

193
00:11:22,139 --> 00:11:23,015
What?

194
00:11:23,974 --> 00:11:27,144
Are we going to get in front of the camera
and say it all on social media?

195
00:11:27,728 --> 00:11:28,646
[Erica] No.

196
00:11:30,439 --> 00:11:32,316
We are going to hold a press conference.

197
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:34,026
That's where we'll admit everything.

198
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:35,486
A press conference?!

199
00:11:36,404 --> 00:11:39,865
A simple video won’t be enough for Edong.

200
00:11:40,574 --> 00:11:43,327
You’ve seen how he’s been torturing us.

201
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:47,123
The bigger the spectacle, the better.

202
00:11:47,873 --> 00:11:50,543
[huffs] You really
just want to humiliate me?

203
00:11:51,460 --> 00:11:53,879
Beth, I don't want
to humiliate or hurt you.

204
00:11:53,963 --> 00:11:56,132
This is nothing personal,

205
00:11:56,757 --> 00:11:59,009
but it involves all of us.

206
00:11:59,093 --> 00:12:03,806
[melancholic music playing]

207
00:12:03,889 --> 00:12:06,434
Do you know how proud I am of my daughter?

208
00:12:08,227 --> 00:12:11,856
She’s just a kid,
but she understands how the world works.

209
00:12:13,274 --> 00:12:15,025
She is not afraid to speak up,

210
00:12:15,109 --> 00:12:17,069
especially when she knows what's right.

211
00:12:20,030 --> 00:12:23,033
Everyone says she takes after me.

212
00:12:24,118 --> 00:12:25,453
I believed it.

213
00:12:27,455 --> 00:12:28,706
But that's not true.

214
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:32,668
She doesn't take after me.

215
00:12:34,837 --> 00:12:40,092
Chloe is so much better than I am.

216
00:12:40,176 --> 00:12:43,804
[melancholic music continues]

217
00:12:43,888 --> 00:12:46,140
If she were in my shoes before,

218
00:12:47,850 --> 00:12:50,311
she wouldn’t have
bent to Celestino’s will.

219
00:12:52,646 --> 00:12:57,067
She wouldn't lie about that goddamn watch.

220
00:12:57,151 --> 00:13:00,613
[melancholic music continues]

221
00:13:00,696 --> 00:13:01,655
Fuck!

222
00:13:03,699 --> 00:13:07,161
Damn it, here's the truth.

223
00:13:11,582 --> 00:13:15,002
I lied before because…

224
00:13:16,754 --> 00:13:21,258
I thought I had to do that…

225
00:13:22,468 --> 00:13:24,803
…to put Louisa’s killer behind bars..

226
00:13:24,887 --> 00:13:27,556
[melancholic music continues]

227
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:28,641
But…

228
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:32,645
when I think about saying that to Chloe,

229
00:13:35,314 --> 00:13:37,900
I know she'd be
disappointed in her mother.

230
00:13:40,361 --> 00:13:41,529
[sobs]

231
00:13:41,612 --> 00:13:44,949
I know that her trust
in me would be shattered.

232
00:13:47,618 --> 00:13:49,912
Just thinking about it now hurts so much.

233
00:13:50,871 --> 00:13:51,914
[sobs]

234
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:58,170
Beth, like you said, Chloe is smart.

235
00:13:58,254 --> 00:14:00,548
If you explain it to her,
she will understand.

236
00:14:00,631 --> 00:14:02,216
You don't understand!

237
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:05,594
You'll never understand
because you don't have any kids!

238
00:14:07,638 --> 00:14:09,557
You don't even have anyone in your life!

239
00:14:10,224 --> 00:14:11,267
You're all alone!

240
00:14:11,350 --> 00:14:12,393
Beth.

241
00:14:12,476 --> 00:14:16,814
[melancholic music continues]

242
00:14:18,816 --> 00:14:19,817
I'm sorry.

243
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:23,195
Sorry.

244
00:14:28,617 --> 00:14:30,202
I don't want to fight anymore.

245
00:14:32,246 --> 00:14:33,956
I'm here, aren't I?

246
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:38,502
We may not need to do that anymore.

247
00:14:39,503 --> 00:14:42,006
Maybe they'll catch Edong soon.

248
00:14:42,089 --> 00:14:46,635
[melancholic music continues]

249
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:51,682
- Beth--
- I said I can't, okay?!

250
00:14:52,141 --> 00:14:54,101
I can't do what you want!

251
00:14:58,856 --> 00:14:59,773
Beth!

252
00:15:00,858 --> 00:15:06,488
[melancholic music swells]

253
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:16,957
- I need to stay here.
- [music fades]

254
00:15:17,541 --> 00:15:22,129
We still have to talk to the prosecutors
to prepare our case against Anton.

255
00:15:22,630 --> 00:15:23,839
[Tom] <i>Whatever you need.</i>

256
00:15:24,506 --> 00:15:25,716
Babe, just say it.

257
00:15:27,176 --> 00:15:29,261
Have you thought about what I said?

258
00:15:29,678 --> 00:15:31,555
There's a case against Anton now.

259
00:15:31,972 --> 00:15:35,726
[Tim] <i>And those videos</i>
<i>you have proving he's abusive?</i>

260
00:15:36,143 --> 00:15:39,271
Those will ensure your win in the case.

261
00:15:40,147 --> 00:15:43,859
I already told you I don't want
those videos to come out, right?

262
00:15:45,778 --> 00:15:47,029
[sighs]

263
00:15:47,112 --> 00:15:47,988
Okay.

264
00:15:48,656 --> 00:15:50,324
If you need us there,

265
00:15:50,407 --> 00:15:51,408
<i>just tell us.</i>

266
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:53,118
No!

267
00:15:53,202 --> 00:15:54,411
Don't come here.

268
00:15:55,162 --> 00:15:56,246
<i>It's not safe.</i>

269
00:15:56,747 --> 00:15:58,082
Oh my god, babe.

270
00:15:58,165 --> 00:16:00,167
You're going through a lot of hardships.

271
00:16:00,751 --> 00:16:02,711
<i>You're fighting against an abusive spouse</i>

272
00:16:03,295 --> 00:16:05,422
and a serial killer at the same time!

273
00:16:06,715 --> 00:16:09,551
That's why I told my mom
not to follow me here either.

274
00:16:11,261 --> 00:16:12,805
I don't want you guys
to get dragged into this.

275
00:16:14,223 --> 00:16:16,767
Edong's also
targeting everyone close to us.

276
00:16:17,977 --> 00:16:23,065
[suspenseful music playing]

277
00:16:23,148 --> 00:16:24,233
There he is.

278
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:28,988
[reporter] <i>TV host Anton Montenegro</i>
<i>gets provisional release</i>

279
00:16:29,488 --> 00:16:33,117
<i>after the court allowed him</i>
<i>to post bail for the three cases</i>

280
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:37,913
<i>filed against him by his wife,</i>
<i>Mel Barrera Montenegro,</i>

281
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:41,917
<i>Attorney Erica Melendez,</i>
<i>and another one of her friends.</i>

282
00:16:42,001 --> 00:16:43,961
[camera shutters clicking]

283
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:46,672
Anton, what do
you think of the judge's decision?

284
00:16:47,089 --> 00:16:49,216
"ANTON MONTENEGRO, PROVISIONAL RELEASE,
GREETED BY SUPPORTERS"

285
00:16:49,299 --> 00:16:51,135
<i>I'm disappointed, of course.</i>

286
00:16:51,844 --> 00:16:53,178
<i>Like I said,</i>

287
00:16:54,013 --> 00:16:57,182
<i>I just defended</i>
<i>myself that's why they got hurt.</i>

288
00:16:57,975 --> 00:16:59,560
And I believe the prosecutors…

289
00:17:00,310 --> 00:17:02,312
made a grave error in judgment.

290
00:17:02,396 --> 00:17:03,856
<i>But I'm ready,</i>

291
00:17:04,773 --> 00:17:07,901
<i>to prove my innocence in court.</i>

292
00:17:08,360 --> 00:17:09,695
Have you talked to Mel?

293
00:17:10,487 --> 00:17:12,906
- [camera shutters clicking]
- I've…

294
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:15,075
actually reached out to my wife.

295
00:17:15,159 --> 00:17:16,326
Many times.

296
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:19,079
- [suspenseful music continues]
- [cameral shutters clicking]

297
00:17:19,163 --> 00:17:20,164
<i>Mel…</i>

298
00:17:21,832 --> 00:17:24,293
<i>I don't know why you're doing this.</i>

299
00:17:25,627 --> 00:17:27,129
<i>But we can still fix this.</i>

300
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:31,633
<i>Despite everything that has happened,</i>

301
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,219
<i>I just want to let you know…</i>

302
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:37,389
<i>I still love you, Mel.</i>

303
00:17:39,224 --> 00:17:41,393
[camera shutters clicking]

304
00:17:41,477 --> 00:17:43,062
[Anton's supporters cheering]

305
00:17:43,145 --> 00:17:45,189
- We love you, Anton!
- We love you, Anton!

306
00:17:45,272 --> 00:17:46,273
- Whoo!
- "WE BELIEVE YOU, ANTON"

307
00:17:46,356 --> 00:17:47,566
- Whoo!
- Whoo!

308
00:17:47,649 --> 00:17:48,776
- We love you!
- We love you!

309
00:17:48,859 --> 00:17:50,402
[reporter] <i>Based on what we saw today,</i>

310
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:53,489
<i>there are still many</i>
<i>who support Anton Montenegro</i>

311
00:17:53,572 --> 00:17:56,533
<i>despite the cases he is facing.</i>

312
00:17:56,617 --> 00:18:00,579
<i>Supporters of so-called</i>
<i>Golden Couple are currently divided</i>

313
00:18:00,662 --> 00:18:03,832
<i>and the issue is expected</i>
<i>to get even more controversial</i>

314
00:18:03,916 --> 00:18:05,542
<i>in the coming weeks.</i>

315
00:18:06,335 --> 00:18:08,837
<i>- Geez! Here we go again!</i>
- "#WeStandWithMel"

316
00:18:08,921 --> 00:18:12,049
<i>This is why so many</i>
<i>women are afraid to speak out</i>

317
00:18:12,132 --> 00:18:14,593
<i>because no one would believe them!</i>

318
00:18:14,676 --> 00:18:17,554
<i>You're so cruel for victim blaming Mel!</i>

319
00:18:17,638 --> 00:18:18,806
<i>And seriously?!</i>

320
00:18:18,889 --> 00:18:22,518
<i>Just because Anton's</i>
<i>handsome and looks like a "green flag"</i>

321
00:18:22,601 --> 00:18:25,729
<i>you're so convinced he can't hurt a fly?</i>

322
00:18:25,813 --> 00:18:27,481
<i>Oh, come on, people!</i>

323
00:18:27,564 --> 00:18:31,235
<i>Stop this toxic fanaticism! Please!</i>

324
00:18:31,318 --> 00:18:32,778
<i>I stand with Mel.</i>

325
00:18:32,861 --> 00:18:33,946
<i>- Oh, come on!</i>
- "#BoycottMel #YourStylesTrash"

326
00:18:34,029 --> 00:18:36,865
<i>We're not born yesterday!</i>
[scoffs] <i>You can't fool us!</i>

327
00:18:36,949 --> 00:18:38,909
<i>Hey, Celebrity Stylist Mel!</i>

328
00:18:38,992 --> 00:18:40,661
<i>Your cover's trash just like your style!</i>

329
00:18:40,744 --> 00:18:43,997
<i>Stop making stuff up just</i>
<i>because you got caught cheating!</i>

330
00:18:44,081 --> 00:18:45,332
<i>You're making my blood boil!</i>

331
00:18:45,415 --> 00:18:47,042
"@SintaOfficialPage
WORKS TO PROTECT WOMEN'S RIGHTS

332
00:18:47,126 --> 00:18:48,585
AND AMPLIFY THE VOICES OF SURVIVORS

333
00:18:48,669 --> 00:18:50,295
WHO HAVE LONG BEEN
SILENCED BY FEAR AND STIGMA."

334
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:53,423
<i>- It's so unfair! Mel's so mean!</i>
- "BoycottMel #AntonNotGuilty"

335
00:18:53,507 --> 00:18:55,968
<i>What if Anton ends up in jail?</i>

336
00:18:56,051 --> 00:18:58,679
<i>No, I can't take it!</i>

337
00:18:58,762 --> 00:19:00,430
<i>I've been losing sleep, guys.</i>

338
00:19:00,514 --> 00:19:03,684
<i>Because what if</i>
<i>Anton really ends up in jail?!</i>

339
00:19:03,767 --> 00:19:05,394
<i>I can't take it!</i>

340
00:19:05,477 --> 00:19:07,479
[music becomes ominous]

341
00:19:07,563 --> 00:19:10,107
[screaming] Aah!

342
00:19:10,190 --> 00:19:11,066
- [thudding]
- [grunts]

343
00:19:11,150 --> 00:19:13,986
Why?! Why?!

344
00:19:14,069 --> 00:19:16,238
[laughing]

345
00:19:16,321 --> 00:19:19,324
- [objects breaking]
- Why me?!

346
00:19:19,408 --> 00:19:21,243
Why?!

347
00:19:21,326 --> 00:19:23,537
[laughing maniacally]

348
00:19:24,496 --> 00:19:28,625
[manic laughing continues]

349
00:19:30,335 --> 00:19:33,881
Why did you let them stop me?

350
00:19:33,964 --> 00:19:35,340
[fake crying]

351
00:19:35,424 --> 00:19:37,926
[laughing maniacally]

352
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:40,012
[eerie music playing]

353
00:19:40,095 --> 00:19:44,892
- [objects thudding]
- [laughing maniacally]

354
00:19:46,685 --> 00:19:48,937
Is this another trial?

355
00:19:49,021 --> 00:19:53,609
[laughing maniacally]

356
00:19:53,692 --> 00:19:55,402
[objects cracking]

357
00:19:55,485 --> 00:19:58,238
[screaming] Argh!

358
00:19:59,114 --> 00:20:05,412
[laughing maniacally]

359
00:20:05,495 --> 00:20:11,210
[eerie music continues]

360
00:20:16,256 --> 00:20:19,259
[music turns unsettling]

361
00:20:19,343 --> 00:20:22,596
Why must you always test me?!

362
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:29,436
[laughing maniacally]

363
00:20:31,104 --> 00:20:33,523
Why did you even let me live,

364
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:37,903
if you were only going
to put a stop to my mission?

365
00:20:40,072 --> 00:20:46,578
[laughing, crying]

366
00:20:46,662 --> 00:20:51,792
[unsettling music continues]

367
00:20:56,296 --> 00:21:00,300
I just want to correct their mistakes.

368
00:21:07,140 --> 00:21:09,351
That's my mission.

369
00:21:12,729 --> 00:21:14,273
[dramatic music sting]

370
00:21:21,446 --> 00:21:25,409
[dramatic music stings]

371
00:21:28,370 --> 00:21:30,998
[unsettling music intensifies]

372
00:21:31,081 --> 00:21:35,168
[screaming]

373
00:21:39,381 --> 00:21:41,675
[ominous music sting]

374
00:21:42,509 --> 00:21:45,345
<i>Ma, when I saw</i>
<i>the dead cat, I was so terrified.</i>

375
00:21:45,429 --> 00:21:46,888
<i>Why is he doing this to us, Ma?</i>

376
00:21:46,972 --> 00:21:48,682
<i>We're surrounded by villains.</i>

377
00:21:48,765 --> 00:21:50,350
<i>I don't want you to get hurt.</i>

378
00:21:50,434 --> 00:21:51,935
<i>I don't want you to be involved, Uncle.</i>

379
00:21:52,019 --> 00:21:54,938
<i>We are surrounded by</i>
<i>people who wants to punish us.</i>

380
00:21:55,022 --> 00:21:57,107
<i>You're nothing</i>
<i>without me! I'll destroy you!</i>

381
00:21:57,190 --> 00:21:58,775
<i>And I feel like we're just waiting</i>

382
00:21:58,859 --> 00:22:00,777
<i>to see which one of them strikes first.</i>

383
00:22:00,861 --> 00:22:05,282
<i>The demons may send</i>
<i>angels to protect sinners,</i>

384
00:22:05,365 --> 00:22:09,453
<i>I won't stop until I complete my mission.</i>
